OL,7,FSophia, 11, was visiting the park with
OL,8,Fher friends and her parents. She said:
OL,9,F"You just heard screaming. The
OL,10,Frollercoaster went up and one of the
OL,11,Fchildren hit their face.
OL,13,F"We'd just come off the ghost train,
OL,14,Fand we saw ambulances rushing in. You
OL,15,Fcould hear screams, and you could see
OL,16,Fthat they had hit their face(s)."
OL,18,FSam's friend, John-Paul Baylis,
OL,19,Fdescribed hearing "horrific screams".
OL,20,FHis son, Ethan, was on the
OL,21,Frollercoaster.
